                "href": "/profile/Tyler-Brown-55"
            },
            "answer_text": "America has done plenty of shitty things. Internment of Americans during WWII for being of \u2018Japanese\u2019 ancestry (giving up a bit of our moral high-ground,) our part in the Afro-European Slave Trade, just about everything we did to the Native Americans, pre-Civil Rights treatment of black people, anti-Irish racism, classicism out the ass, white supremacy, inciting a foreign civil war for our own benefit (multiple times), using the Chinese to build our railroads, being dicks to Canada and Mexico at various points in our history, The Great White Hope (a boxing thing), hell we were probably even at fault in the Boston Massacre/Riot. Do we recognize that we\u2019ve done plenty of wrong? Yes. Do we wish these hadn\u2019t been done, or regret that they are in our history? Yes. Do we feel shame? No. Most Americans either recognize that we are not accountable for the sins of our fathers, and get on with our lives, or aren\u2019t ever forced to face the sins of their fathers for one reason or another. Only a small percentage of (predominantly white) Americans feel the need to make reparations for what their ancestors did, and from what I\u2019ve observed they draw derision from both sides of the aisle. ",
